episodes.title: Gardens
episodes.plot: Stephen Fry glances gleefully at gardens and other subjects starting with the letter G in this extended show. With David Mitchell, Rob Brydon, Dara O Briain and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: G-Animals
episodes.plot: Stephen Fry and Alan Davies are joined by a bumper crop of Bantermeisters as they discuss animals beginning with the letter G - from gerbils to giraffes, geese to gulls. With Bill Bailey, Sean Lock, Sandi Toksvig and John Hodgman.

episodes.title: Games
episodes.plot: Stephen Fry and his guests get gladiatorial in this edition of the quiz when they tackle the topic of games. Regular player Alan Davies is joined by challengers Phill Jupitus, Sean Lock and Liza Tarbuck.

episodes.title: Geography
episodes.plot: Stephen Fry maps out the agenda as Jo Brand, Rob Brydon, Jimmy Carr and Alan Davies navigate questions on the topic of Geography. Who is to the right of Ghengis Khan? and Why are there no snakes in Ireland? are amongst the questions.

episodes.title: Groovy
episodes.plot: Comedy quiz show where the guests get points for being interesting. Stephen Fry guarantees you a groovy Christmas, with David Tennant, Bill Bailey, Lee Mack and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Genius
episodes.plot: Genial host Stephen Fry ponders the topic of genius with guests Graham Norton, David Mitchell, Dara O'Briain and Alan Davies. Even simple questions such as "How old are you?" can be a cause of consternation in this quiz show.

episodes.title: Girls and Boys
episodes.plot: "What does your granny have in common with a Killer Whale?" is amongst the unusual questions posed by host Stephen Fry as he tackles the subject of girls and boys with guests Sandi Toksvig, Ronni Ancona, Jack Dee and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Germany
episodes.plot: Comedy quiz show where the guests get more points for being interesting. Stephen Fry gladly gravitates towards Germany. He is joined by Jo Brand, Rob Brydon, Sean Lock and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Gallimaufrey
episodes.plot: Things get even more confusing than usual in this edition of the quite interesting quiz when host Stephen Fry introduces guests Phill Jupitus, Hugh Dennis, Andy Hamilton and Alan Davies to a gallimaufry of gingambobs.

episodes.title: Greats
episodes.plot: Quiz show where guests get more points for being interesting. Stephen Fry gets to grips with the greats, with Jo Brand, David Mitchell, Sean Lock and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Gifts
episodes.plot: In this edition of the quite interesting quiz show genial host Stephen Fry bestows his knowledge of gifts upon Alan Davies, Clive Anderson, Jimmy Carr and Jan Ravens as they attempt to accumulate point-based presents.

episodes.title: Gravity
episodes.plot: "What's the use of an underwater weighing machine?" and "Why did Fosbury flop?" are some of the questions floated by host Stephen Fry as guests Barry Humphries, Bill Bailey, Rich Hall and Alan Davies are pressed on the topic of gravity.

episodes.title: Gothic
episodes.plot: Host Stephen Fry blows the cobwebs away when he goes all gothic in this edition of the popular quiz. Gargoyles and grotesques are amongst the topics to be dissected by guests Sue Perkins, Jimmy Carr, Jack Dee and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Greeks
episodes.plot: Comedy quiz show where the guests get more points for being interesting. Stephen Fry gets to grips with Greeks, with Clive Anderson, Phill Jupitus, Rich Hall and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Green
episodes.plot: Comedy quiz show where the guests get more points for being interesting. Stephen Fry goes all green with Jeremy Clarkson, Bill Bailey, Danny Baker and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Geometry
episodes.plot: Comedy quiz where the guests get more points for being interesting. Stephen Fry tackles geometry with the help of Johnny Vegas, David Mitchell, Rob Brydon and Alan Davies.

episodes.title: Compilation 1
episodes.plot: A hotch-potch of moments from the G series with Stephen Fry, Alan Davies and their guests.

episodes.title: Compilation 2
episodes.plot: A hotch-potch of moments from the G series with Stephen Fry, Alan Davies and their guests.
